               <p>BENJAMIN WYON. I live in Nassau-street, Soho. On the 15th of May, about ten o'clock in the evening, I was walking in <placeName id="t18340515-147-crimeloc803">Wardour-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18340515-147-crimeloc803" type="placeName" value="Wardour-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18340515-147-crimeloc803" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340515-147-off801 t18340515-147-crimeloc803"></join> - I felt my pocket move - I felt for my handkerchief, it was gone - I turned round, and saw two <rs id="t18340515-147-viclabel804" type="occupation">boy</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340515-147-victim1325 t18340515-147-viclabel804"></join>s close behind me - I accused them of having my handkerchief - I took hold of one, he denied it - the prisoner, who was the other boy, ran off - I and my brother pursued and caught him - we gave him in charge.</p>
